
/*
 * // The Hyperlambda code below demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a destination node's children collection. The [add] slot takes an expression pointing to a destination node and adds the result of its child node expressions to the destination node. In this example, it adds all child nodes of the [.body] node to the destination node specified by the expression in the [add] slot.
 * // 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the destination node's children collection.
 * // 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves all child nodes of the [.body] node.
 */
add:x:+/*
   get-nodes:x:@.body/*
